[Spoilers Aired] I miss the charm, mystery, and romance of Season One
WRITING.TEXT:
We're three episodes into Season 2, and I'm really missing Season 1.
What initially drew my interest in the novel/show was 1) Time travel, and 2) Early-modern life of the Highlands.
When I first heard there was going to be a show based on the novels, I was skeptical. I thought it was going to be shit, frankly.
But thankfully, I was very wrong.
Season 1 had all of the: charm, mystery, intrigue, and romance of the novels. Not only that, but the TV show is *very* addictive.
Other than The People v. O.J. Simpson: American Crime Story, I can't think of another show that aired in recent years that is as addictive as Outlander Season One.
I don't think there was a single episode in the first season that bored me. Tuning in was always a joy.
Season 2 has been..a bit of a bore.
Pre-revolutionary France just isn't as appealing to me as the Scottish plots.
This isn't a knock against the show; it's still good..just not as addictive to me at the moment.
I know the show is just following the novels' plots. The French plot of DiA bored me as well.
[Spoilers DiA](/s "I know we're going to return to Scotland, and I'm just waiting for that.")
I miss the people, places, and scenery of Season One. I miss the mud and grime of the Highlands over the pomp of Paris.
End rant.
